      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index benchmark synthesis — multi-study aggregate",
      "description": "A synthesis of multiple prior studies examining power-law hemolysis damage models (Giersiepen, Zhang, Taskin formulations) applied to centrifugal pump geometries similar to the FDA benchmark. This node aggregates findings from seven independent experimental and computational campaigns published between 2008 and 2021, providing a consolidated reference distribution of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values across operating envelopes comparable to the CPB COU. The synthesis was conducted by the credibility assessment team and serves as a key intermediate anchor for the claim that CFD-predicted hemolysis indices fall within clinically acceptable bounds.",
