      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented QA procedures and regression test suite.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 used under FDA-registered QMS. Regression tests covering 47 benchmark cases executed prior to study. Version control via Git with tagged release. Achieves Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical flow problems demonstrate solver convergence consistent with documented spatial and temporal discretization schemes.",
      "rationale": "Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity benchmarks confirm second-order spatial accuracy. Temporal discretization verified via manufactured solutions. Results consistent with published solver documentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for QoI hemolysis index must be less than 5% at the operating point of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted: coarse (2.1M cells), medium (5.8M cells), fine (14.2M cells). GCI for NIH at 3.5 L/min/4000 RPM is 3.1%. Richardson extrapolation applied. Discretization error within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be replicated in the CFD model within ±5% of measured values.",
      "rationale": "PIV experiments conducted with blood analog fluid (36% glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 cP at 37°C). Inlet flow rate controlled to ±1.2%, rotational speed to ±0.3%. Boundary conditions matched within tolerance. Pump geometry digitized via CT scan with 0.1 mm resolution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized RMS error between CFD-predicted and PIV-measured velocity magnitudes must not exceed 10% across the impeller passage cross-section.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error of 4.3% computed over 1,847 PIV measurement points in the impeller passage. Peak local discrepancy of 12% observed in the tip clearance region, consistent with known PIV measurement uncertainty in high-shear zones. Overall comparison satisfies acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (velocity fields, shear stress distributions) must be mechanistically linked to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis index) via an accepted damage accumulation model.",
      "rationale": "Lagrangian particle tracking applied to converged velocity and shear stress fields. Power-law hemolysis damage model (Zhang et al. 2011) relates scalar shear stress and exposure time to hemolysis probability. Model form is consistent with FDA guidance on hemolysis prediction. QoIs are directly relevant to COU endpoint."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
